  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "This may just be an issue of me misunderstanding the documentation, but the docs say \r\n\r\n`Buidler detects if typescript and ts-node are installed in its npm project, and automatically enables TypeScript support.`\r\n\r\nI didn't know this when I started my project the first time, and so I have now re-initialized the project to make sure that I'm able to get typescript working smoothly by following the instructions to the letter.\r\n\r\nI was thinking it might be more convenient for people if typescript was an option in the project initialization instead of being something that is automagically detected from the installed modules.",
